{
  "stem": "13690.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And it was written down that 'This and this family gave so many of so many.' In other words, they knew-- or they were probably denouncing that, let's say, if a family was a well-to-do family, that that family probably has more than one piece or two pieces of fur, so to say, to be delivered.",
      "word_count": 56
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I don't know exactly who did, but they must have some kind of a system to find out who is well, and who is poor-- some-- I could not imagine-- even if somebody will be denouncing it, seemingly, that they were threatening that they do know.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Could possibly also be that-- that they did not know, and they're just pretending that they do know.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I do remember exactly an incident when it comes to this question of furs.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "As I said, the people-- most of the people in the town were religious people.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And, being religious, you had to go twice to-- to the prayer-- for prayers to the synagogue.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And at one time-- which, of course, all the synagogue was destroyed in 1939, with the exception of the big synagogue.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But then, they established small synagogues in private houses, because you're not supposed to just gather together.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Being that our customs is that by having 10 people you could establish a formal prayer.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So a man was walking to a prayer.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he was probably-- was heavy [INAUDIBLE] this man, a sick man, and he was wearing fur pants.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the Germans spotted that he is wearing pants which are fur-lined.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] This was at the time when the ordinance was that all the furs has to be delivered to the Germans.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They did not ask him to take off the-- the pants.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
